# Design News & Notes Web App

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ with App Router and TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- shadcn/ui for component library
- React Query for data fetching
- Markdown support for note editor

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer server components when possible
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Keep components under 200 lines
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all props
- Avoid inline styles, use Tailwind classes

## Component Structure
- One component per file
- Export components as named exports
- Place interfaces above component definition
- Use destructured props with TypeScript types

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (NewsCard, CategoryNav)
- Files: kebab-case (news-card.tsx, category-nav.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with 'use' prefix (useNewsFilter)
- Types: PascalCase with descriptive names

## Import Order
1. React and Next.js imports
2. Third-party libraries
3. Internal utilities and hooks
4. Component imports
5. Type imports
6. Style imports

## Data Fetching
- Use Server Components for initial data
- React Query for client-side data management
- Implement proper loading and error states
- Cache appropriately based on data volatility

## Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns
- Maintain consistent spacing scale
- Implement responsive design mobile-first
- Support dark mode using CSS variables

## Performance
- Lazy load below-fold content
- Optimize images with next/image
- Implement code splitting
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Debounce search and filter inputs

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain focus management
- Test with screen readers

## Error Handling
- Always catch async errors
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors for debugging
- Implement retry mechanisms
- Graceful degradation

## Security
- Sanitize user input
- Validate data on client and server
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Escape rendered HTML content

